aptured traffic taps from Envoy.\n\n### gRPC Health Checking Protocol (grpc/grpc)\n\nThe gRPC repository includes the standard gRPC Health Checking Protocol (grpc_health_v1):\n\n**Health Service** - Defined in src/proto/grpc/health/v1/health.proto. This is the standard gRPC health checking service that provides two RPC methods:\n- Check: Performs a one-time health check for a service\n- Watch: Streams health status changes for a service\n\nImplementation files for the Health service in gRPC:\n- src/cpp/server/health/health_check_service.cc - Core implementation\n- src/cpp/server/health/default_health_check_service.cc - Default implementation\n\n### Cross-Organization Usage\n\nThese services represent the interface between Envoy (the data plane) and management servers (xDS providers) using a common gRPC-based protocol. The Health service is used by Envoy and other gRPC services to report their operational status. Together, they form the fundamental building blocks for service mesh control planes and gRPC infrastructure.\n"
}
