  "text": "## Cross-Organization gRPC Service Definition Discovery\n\n### Envoy Data Plane API (envoyproxy/data-plane-api)\n\nThe data-plane-api repository contains gRPC service definitions for the xDS (service discovery) protocol and supporting Envoy services. These services are organized across multiple proto files and versions (v2, v2alpha, and v3).\n\n#### xDS Discovery Services (Core)\nThese are the primary service discovery services used by Envoy and other xDS clients:\n\n1. **ClusterDiscoveryService (CDS)** - Defined in envoy/service/cluster/v3/cds.proto and envoy/api/v2/cds.proto. Provides cluster configuration discovery.\n\n2. **EndpointDiscoveryService (EDS)** - Defined in envoy/service/endpoint/v3/eds.proto and envoy/api/v2/eds.proto. Provides endpoint/load assignment discovery.\n\n3. **ListenerDiscoveryService (LDS)** - Defined in envoy/service/listener/v3/lds.proto and envoy/api/v2/lds.proto. Provides listener configuration discovery.\n\n4. **RouteDiscoveryService (RDS)** - Defined in envoy/service/route/v3/rds.proto and envoy/api/v2/rds.proto. Provides route configuration discovery.\n\n5. **SecretDiscoveryService (SDS)** - Defined in envoy/service/secret/v3/sds.proto and envoy/service/discovery/v2/sds.proto. Provides secret (TLS certificate) discovery.\n\n6. **VirtualHostDiscoveryService (VHDS)** - Defined in envoy/service/route/v3/rds.proto and envoy/api/v2/rds.proto. Provides virtual host configuration discovery.\n\n7. **ScopedRoutesDiscoveryService (SRDS)** - Defined in envoy/service/route/v3/srds.proto and envoy/api/v2/srds.proto. Provides scoped route configuration discovery.\n\n8. **LocalityEndpointDiscoveryService (LEDS)** - Defined in envoy/service/endpoint/v3/leds.proto. Provides locality-specific endpoint discovery.\n\n9. **RuntimeDiscoveryService (RTDS)** - Defined in envoy/service/runtime/v3/rtds.proto and envoy/service/discovery/v2/rtds.proto. Provides runtime configuration discovery.\n\n10. **AggregatedDiscoveryService (ADS)** - Defined in envoy/service/discovery/v3/ads.proto and envoy/service/discovery/v2/ads.proto. Provides multiplexed access to all xDS services.\n\n#### Supporting Services\nThese services provide additional functionality for Envoy:\n\n11. **ClientStatusDiscoveryService (CSDS)** - Defined in envoy/service/status/v3/csds.proto and envoy/service/status/v2/csds.proto. Allows clients to report their configuration status to management servers.\n\n12. **AccessLogService (ALS)** - Defined in envoy/service/accesslog/v3/als.proto and envoy/service/accesslog/v2/als.proto. Streams access logs to an external logging service.\n\n13. **MetricsService** - Defined in envoy/service/metrics/v3/metrics_service.proto and envoy/service/metrics/v2/metrics_service.proto. Streams metrics to an external metrics service.\n\n14. **LoadReportingService (LRS)** - Defined in envoy/service/load_stats/v3/lrs.proto and envoy/service/load_stats/v2/lrs.proto. Reports load statistics to the management server.\n\n15. **RateLimitService (RLS)** - Defined in envoy/service/ratelimit/v3/rls.proto and envoy/service/ratelimit/v2/rls.proto. Provides rate limiting decisions.\n\n16. **RateLimitQuotaService (RLQS)** - Defined in envoy/service/rate_limit_quota/v3/rlqs.proto. Manages rate limit quota allocations.\n\n17. **Authorization** - Defined in envoy/service/auth/v3/external_auth.proto. Provides authorization checks for incoming requests.\n\n18. **ExternalProcessor** - Defined in envoy/service/ext_proc/v3/external_processor.proto. Allows external processing of HTTP requests and responses.\n\n19. **HealthDiscoveryService (HDS)** - Defined in envoy/service/health/v3/hds.proto. Enables Envoy instances to perform health checks on behalf of the management server.\n\n20. **NetworkExternalProcessor** - Defined in envoy/service/network_ext_proc/v3/network_external_processor.proto. Provides external processing capabilities for L4 network traffic.\n\n21. **TapSinkService** - Defined in envoy/service/tap/v2alpha/tap.proto. Receives captured traffic taps from Envoy.\n\n### gRPC Health Checking Protocol (grpc/grpc)\n\nThe gRPC repository includes the standard gRPC Health Checking Protocol (grpc_health_v1):\n\n**Health Service** - Defined in src/proto/grpc/health/v1/health.proto. This is the standard gRPC health checking service that provides two RPC methods:\n- Check: Performs a one-time health check for a service\n- Watch: Streams health status changes for a service\n\nImplementation files for the Health service in gRPC:\n- src/cpp/server/health/health_check_service.cc - Core implementation\n- src/cpp/server/health/default_health_check_service.cc - Default implementation\n\n### Cross-Organization Usage\n\nThese services represent the interface between Envoy (the data plane) and management servers (xDS providers) using a common gRPC-based protocol. The Health service is used by Envoy and other gRPC services to report their operational status. Together, they form the fundamental building blocks for service mesh control planes and gRPC infrastructure.\n"
}

